{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:26:07.602310", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and methodology\\n- Collected end-to-end reachability snapshot across lab nodes.\\n- Verified critical data-plane reachability (ICMP) from user hosts to DNS and a representative web server.\\n- Inspected IP configuration on user hosts.\\n- Verified OSPF adjacencies and routing tables on core and distribution routers, and on the server access router.\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- The routed network (OSPF core, distribution, server access) is healthy: adjacencies are Full, routes to all expected subnets are present, and server farm connectivity is normal.\\n- A single user host, host_2_1_1_1, is not functioning due to missing IPv4 configuration, causing local “Network is unreachable” errors. Other hosts in the same distribution domain show healthy intra-subnet connectivity, isolating the problem to this specific endpoint.\\n\\nDetailed findings\\n\\n1) Reachability tests\\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server (10.200.0.2): OK\\n  Evidence: 4/4 replies, avg ~3.78 ms\\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): OK\\n  Evidence: 4/4 replies, avg ~3.65 ms\\n- host_2_1_1_1 -> dns_server (10.200.0.2): FAIL\\n  Evidence: ping returned “Network is unreachable”\\n- host_2_1_1_1 -> web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): FAIL\\n  Evidence: ping returned “Network is unreachable”\\n- DNS server and web servers can reach each other within 10.200.0.0/24: OK\\n  Evidence: dns_server -> web_server_0: 0% loss, ~1.3 ms avg\\n  web_server_{1..3} -> web_server_0: 0% loss, ~1.1–1.6 ms avg\\n- Hosts under 10.2.1.0/24 (other than host_2_1_1_1) show intra-subnet reachability:\\n  Evidence: host_2_1_1_2 -> host_2_1_2_2: 0% loss, ~2.53 ms avg\\n           host_2_1_2_1 -> host_2_1_2_2: 0% loss, ~1.78 ms avg\\n\\nNote: Many entries in the bulk reachability snapshot are “unknown” due to sampling; this is not indicative of failure.\\n\\n2) Host configurations\\n- host_1_1_1_1\\n  IP: 10.1.1.2/24, default via 10.1.1.1, DNS reachable: OK\\n- host_2_1_1_1\\n  No IPv4 address configured on eth0; no routes present\\n  Evidence:\\n  - ip addr: eth0 has no “inet” entry\\n  - ip route: empty\\n  - ping failures return “Network is unreachable”\\n\\n3) OSPF control plane and routing tables\\n- Core and distribution routers show Full neighbor adjacencies consistent with topology.\\n  Evidence: “show ip ospf neighbor” on router_core_{1,2,3}, switch_dist_{1_1,2_1}, and switch_server_access indicate Full.\\n- IP routing tables include all expected user and server subnets with OSPF-learned paths:\\n  - router_core_1: OSPF routes to 10.1.1.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24, 10.200.0.0/24 via appropriate core/distribution links.\\n  - router_core_2, router_core_3: symmetric OSPF routes.\\n  - switch_dist_1_1: 10.1.1.0/24 directly connected (br0), other subnets via core.\\n  - switch_dist_2_1: 10.2.1.0/24 directly connected (br0), other subnets via core.\\n  - switch_server_access: 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected, user subnets via core.\\n\\n4) Localization of fault\\n- The failure is localized to host_2_1_1_1:\\n  - It lacks an IP address and default route, resulting in immediate local routing failure before the packet can reach the L3 gateway.\\n  - Distribution switch switch_dist_2_1 has the 10.2.1.0/24 network up and advertised via OSPF; other hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 communicate successfully, indicating the L2/L3 path is healthy.\\n\\n5) Root cause hypothesis\\n- Misconfiguration on host_2_1_1_1: static IP addressing was not applied (per design, hosts should be statically addressed in 10.<core>.<dist>.0/24 with gateway on the distribution switch and DNS pointing to the central server). The absence of any IPv4 configuration on host_2_1_1_1 directly causes “Network is unreachable” for all off-host traffic.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Network-wide OSPF control plane and server farm connectivity are normal.\\n- The only detected anomaly is a host-level misconfiguration on host_2_1_1_1 (missing IPv4 address and routes), causing loss of connectivity from that endpoint. No evidence of faults on the distribution switches, core, or server access router., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='7ddb66df-0550-4f6d-ba46-4882ab3a7efa'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
